message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper proposes a new approach based on Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNN) for thrombus segmentation in post-operative CTA images. This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered in the computer science sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper focuses on medical imaging and specifically deals with abdominal aortic aneurysms (AAA), which falls under the medical imaging (cs.MED) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for image segmentation is a common technique in the field of neuroscience (cs.NEURON).
